<br>
Still this system means that the losers get their vote counted more than the &quot;winners&quot;.  Basically it means that if I rank the eventual winner last my vote gets counted 5 or 6 or 7 times while the person who ranked the eventual winner first only had their vote counted once.<br>
<br>
It doesn't make any sense that people should have a say on more than a one vote for one person basis.  I don't think our current method works that way, but this alternative merely provides for tyranny of the minority in a different light.  Just because I vote for the green party (hypothetically speaking) does not mean that I should also be able to vote for the democratic candidate, when the green party cadidate loses.  <br>
<br>
I personally can't see how it is fair and equitable.  It seems to me that this system would be an over correction and ultimately just as bad as the current situation.<br>
<br>
Locke<br>
<br>
